In this updated code, a modal curtain with the class "veil" is added above the gallery content. The `window.addEventListener('load', ...)` function is used to hide the modal curtain once the page has loaded completely. Initially, the curtain has an opacity of 1 and `pointer-events: none` so that it doesn't interfere with interacting with the gallery. When the page finishes loading, the modal curtain's opacity is changed to 0 by adding the "hide" class, and `pointer-events` are set to none to allow interaction with the gallery.

